import React from 'react';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';

export default function App() {
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm();
  const onSubmit = data => console.log(data);
  console.log(errors);
  
  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <input type="text" placeholder="Name" {...register("Name", {maxLength: 80})} />
      <select {...register("Gender", { required: true })}>
        <option value="Woman">Woman</option>
        <option value="Man">Man</option>
        <option value="Transgender">Transgender</option>
        <option value="Non-binary/non-conforming">Non-binary/non-conforming</option>
        <option value="Prefer not to respond">Prefer not to respond</option>
      </select>
      <select {...register("Age", { required: true })}>
        <option value="18-24">18-24</option>
        <option value=" 25-34"> 25-34</option>
        <option value=" 35-44"> 35-44</option>
        <option value=" 45-54"> 45-54</option>
        <option value=" 55-64"> 55-64</option>
        <option value=" 65+"> 65+</option>
      </select>
      <select {...register("Year Graduated ", { required: true })}>
        <option value="2022">2022</option>
        <option value=" 2021"> 2021</option>
        <option value=" 2020"> 2020</option>
        <option value=" 2019"> 2019</option>
        <option value=" 2018"> 2018</option>
        <option value=" 2017"> 2017</option>
        <option value=" 2016"> 2016</option>
        <option value=" 2015"> 2015</option>
        <option value=" 2014"> 2014</option>
      </select>

      <input {...register("Program", { required: true })} type="radio" value="BE" />
      <input {...register("Program", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" FE" />
      <input type="number" placeholder="Experience (in years)" {...register("Experience (in years)", {required: true, max: 30, min: 0})} />
      <select {...register("Degree", { required: true })}>
        <option value="NO DEGREE">NO DEGREE</option>
        <option value=" NOT CS RELATED"> NOT CS RELATED</option>
        <option value=" CS RELATED"> CS RELATED</option>
      </select>
      <select {...register("State:", { required: true })}>
        <option value="STATE">STATE</option>
      </select>
      <input type="number" placeholder="Salary (yearly)" {...register("Salary (yearly)", {required: true})} />
      <input type="text" placeholder="Position Title" {...register("Position Title", {required: true})} />

      <input {...register("Type of Employment", { required: true })} type="radio" value="Part-Time" />
      <input {...register("Type of Employment", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" Full-Time" />
      <input {...register("Type of Employment", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" Contract" />
      <input {...register("Type of Employment", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" Temporary" />
      <input {...register("Type of Employment", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" " />

      <input {...register("Did you negotiate? ", { required: true })} type="radio" value="Yes" />
      <input {...register("Did you negotiate? ", { required: true })} type="radio" value=" No" />
      <input type="text" placeholder="Company Name" {...register("Company Name", {})} />

      <input type="submit" />
    </form>
  );
}
